trend_summary: Across the series, modest infill and edge-of-town subdivision raise built coverage slightly, but forests and fields still dominate. Development clusters grow mainly along the north-south highway and around the historic centre, while riverbank vegetation actually increases. Net trend: slow suburban sprawl without large industrial footprints.
notable_changes: Gradual outward expansion of the central town core in all directions.
New residential cul-de-sacs appear along the main highway corridor.
Small farmland parcels convert to housing, especially in the southeast quadrant.
Riverbank shows widened vegetated buffer and less bare soil over time.
Minor roadway realignments and added intersections improve regional access.
